Journal Content License

The MIT terms above cover the website code, layouts, styles, and scripts. They
do NOT cover the articles.

Authors retain copyright of their individual works. Every article is licensed
separately, and each article page states its own terms. Do not rely on this
file for any particular article -- check the article.

As published to date, every article in this repository is licensed under one
of the following. None of them permits commercial reuse:

  - CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 -- 86 articles
  - CC BY-SA 4.0    --  3 articles

These are the terms their authors granted during the journal's OJS era
(2012-2026). The journal cannot relicense that work retroactively, so the
archive will always carry them.

Articles accepted through the journal's GitHub-based open-review workflow are
intended to be published under CC BY 4.0, which does permit commercial reuse
with attribution. No article has yet been published under that workflow, so no
article in this repository currently carries those terms.

Machine-readable terms for each article are in its record under _articles/, in
the `license` field, and are rendered on the article page and in its citation
metadata.

  CC BY 4.0        https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/
  CC BY-SA 4.0     https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/
  CC BY-NC-SA 4.0  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/
